Hi Mark, were you unable to hazard a guess for even one clue in the puzzle? If so, I agree, that is disheartening. 

However, if, after going through all the across and down clues, you have made even a single educated guess, then you do have a starting point. Frequently I get almost nothing on my first pass, but even a single reasonable guess gives me additional clues for all the words that cross it. Slowly I try to build up from that point. My personal rule is that if I can get even one new letter during a complete pass through the clues, them I am not yet totally stuck. Because that's one new clue. And if I am totally stuck, that's the time to start doing some research. Which I did a lot of, my first few years. It was a long time before I could start a streak.

